or is it&#8230;
Let&#8217;s see.
- in total, 7 watts isn&#8217;t that much for a server, so it&#8217;s green
- but if you look at the number [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a class="tweet-this" href="http://twitter.com/home/?status=www.f43t5.th8.us+to+Green+or+not+to+Green%3F" title="Post to Twitter (www.f43t5.th8.us)"></a><p>Slow? Yes this site is slow. Why? Well it&#8217;s running on a slow <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Server_%28computing%29" title="Server (computing)" rel="wikipedia" class="zem_slink">server</a>. A low energyconsumption, slow server. Yes, A green server. 7 Watts isn&#8217;t that much, so it&#8217;s very green.</p>
<p>or is it&#8230;</p>
<p>Let&#8217;s see.</p>
<p>- in total, 7 watts isn&#8217;t that much for a server, so it&#8217;s green</p>
<p>- but if you look at the number of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visitors_%28program%29" title="Visitors (program)" rel="wikipedia" class="zem_slink">visitors</a> per <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Watt" title="Watt" rel="wikipedia" class="zem_slink">watt</a>, hmmm, not so green at all</p>
<p>- This means I need to get more <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hit_%28internet%29" title="Hit (internet)" rel="wikipedia" class="zem_slink">hits</a>, more visitors</p>
<p>- that would <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mean" title="Mean" rel="wikipedia" class="zem_slink">mean</a> however that the site might get even slower</p>
<p>- or maybe go down alltogether&#8230; that&#8217;s not very green, rather it&#8217;s black&#8230;</p>
<p>So what is it? Green, or not green?</p>
<p><a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0083399" title="Cheers" rel="imdb" class="zem_slink">Cheers</a></p>
